Causes severe drought that - compounded by logging - feeds the largest fire disaster ever observed.
Triggers record rainfall that led to mudslides and $1 billion in estimated damages.
Decimates giant kelp populations along North American coast.
Causes wet anomalies in the spring before warm years and dry anomalies in the spring before cool years.
Results in a drastic 77% decline in penguin populations.
Linked to record low in coverage of Maldive-Chagos coral reefs.
Reduces fish size and growth into 1984.
Reshapes livestock populations through rainfall differences in highlands and lowlands.
Shifts nutrient distribution and results in post-ENSO phytoplankton bloom.
Increases rainfall and drives 5 to 10 times higher seed densities in arid soil.

column1: HEAT WAVE AND WILDFIRES IN RUSSIA
column2: Exacerbates record heat and vast wildfires in Russia through a 'blocking' anticyclone.
Linked to harsh drought that renders India susceptible to other health risks.
Tentatively linked to amplified winter conditions that decimate Napoleon's army in Russia.
Arguably tied to harsh Russian winter that put a quarter of Hitler's troops out of action.
Potentially linked to anomalous southerly ice floes.
Likely tied to extreme desert rainfall that sustain the invading Spaniards.
Draws precipitation away from Australia causing wildfires and low crop yields.
Warms water near present-day Peru drastically reshaping regional fishing patterns.
